Application load balancers - Layer 7 of the OSI stack
Network load balancers - Layer 4 of the OSI stack
Classic load balancers - still covered but not recommended

Use app load balancers for http & https traffic
they are intelligent and application aware

Network LB are best suited to TCP traffic - extreme performance

Classic load balancers - legacy

x-forwarded-for header

exam TIPS
3 types
504 error gateway timed out, trouble shoot the application
IPV4 ip address look at the x-forwarded-header
